15:11.244 --> 15:13.494
real classic-looking
hatchet head.

15:13.538 --> 15:15.288
I think it'll be
a good performer.

15:15.332 --> 15:16.664
- Thank you.

15:16.708 --> 15:18.207
- Jason, you're up.

15:18.251 --> 15:19.167
Please present your hatchet
to the judges.

15:19.210 --> 15:22.128
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:22.172 --> 15:24.172
<i> - I'm a huge fan of cleavers,</i>
<i> and another thing</i>

15:24.215 --> 15:26.966
that you did that I like
is the way this tapers,

15:27.010 --> 15:29.636
putting all the mass
right there at the neck,

15:29.679 --> 15:31.846
which'll support that nicely.

15:31.890 --> 15:34.474
- That's a lot of meat
there, Jason.

15:34.517 --> 15:36.684
Everybody wanted to use
and go for the big hatchet.

15:36.728 --> 15:39.562
Nonetheless though,
nice grind finish to that.

15:39.606 --> 15:41.773
I'm looking forward to it
if it moves forward.

15:41.816 --> 15:43.066
Thank you.

15:43.109 --> 15:44.567
- Ray?

15:44.611 --> 15:48.363
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:48.406 --> 15:50.448
<i> - 30 years of blade-making,</i>

15:50.492 --> 15:52.742
<i> you can show people that</i>
<i> technique really matters.</i>

15:52.786 --> 15:54.452
I like your classic shape
of a hatchet

15:54.496 --> 15:56.996
with your head over here.

15:57.040 --> 15:58.873
Lot of meat there.
The second round,

15:58.917 --> 16:00.249
I'm sure you can work
on that also.

16:00.293 --> 16:01.459
Thank you.

16:01.503 --> 16:03.002
- Adlai, you're up.

16:03.046 --> 16:06.047
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:06.091 --> 16:08.800
<i> - You made some</i>
<i> very different work here,</i>

16:08.843 --> 16:10.802
which I do appreciate.

