So what was your idea
behind it?

16:13.264 --> 16:15.390
- It was just
kind of zenning it out,

16:15.433 --> 16:17.266
just see where
the metal took me.

16:17.310 --> 16:20.812
It was kind of just what popped
into my head at the time.

16:20.855 --> 16:22.271
- I know you were struggling
a little bit there,

16:22.315 --> 16:24.107
but you still
pulled through.

16:24.150 --> 16:26.526
You know, you deserve
a round of applause for that.

16:26.569 --> 16:28.653
- Thank you.

16:28.697 --> 16:32.407
- Well, bladesmiths, the judges
have a decision to make,

16:32.450 --> 16:34.867
so I'm gonna ask you to leave
your hatchets on this table

16:34.911 --> 16:36.160
as you leave the Forge floor.

16:36.204 --> 16:41.791
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:41.835 --> 16:43.751
- I was definitely
expecting a knife.

16:43.795 --> 16:45.503
- Yeah, I was expecting
another knife too.

16:45.547 --> 16:47.839
- Same here.
This was my worst nightmare

16:47.882 --> 16:49.757
coming true
as soon as I saw that billet.

16:49.801 --> 16:51.551
- All right, judges,
let's go ahead

16:51.594 --> 16:53.469
and start with Stephen's
blade on the end, please, Doug.

16:53.513 --> 16:54.929
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:54.973 --> 16:56.514
<i> - Well, Stephen was</i>
<i> trying to go</i>

16:56.558 --> 16:58.433
<i> with two particular ideas</i>
<i> over here,</i>

16:58.476 --> 17:02.228
the head of a hatchet in line
