17:43.897 --> 17:45.855
What the hell?"
[laughs]

17:45.899 --> 17:48.524
- That's 30 years of experience.

17:48.568 --> 17:50.568
<i>- The shape is classic hatchet.</i>

17:50.612 --> 17:53.446
<i> He's exactly at 4 inches,</i>
<i> but I would like to see</i>

17:53.490 --> 17:57.325
this area have been
a little smoother.

17:57.368 --> 17:59.619
I don't mind forge texture.

17:59.662 --> 18:01.871
<i> I just kind of like</i>
<i> more even forge texture.</i>

18:01.915 --> 18:04.582
- Adlai's blade.

18:04.626 --> 18:09.128
<i> - By mistake, Adlai created</i>
<i> an Egyptian axe here,</i>

18:09.172 --> 18:12.423
but the reason they work is,
is it's counterbalanced

18:12.467 --> 18:15.468
by a large handle,
large shaft.

18:15.512 --> 18:18.096
This doesn't have that,
so I mea

18:18.139 --> 18:20.765
holding it out at arm's length,

18:20.809 --> 18:22.517
it just turns in your hand.

18:22.560 --> 18:24.185
There's so much weight
in this head,

18:24.229 --> 18:26.354
so that is a real problem,

18:26.397 --> 18:28.689
but if he put
a large handle on it

18:28.733 --> 18:30.399
and then chopped
that much of it off,

18:30.443 --> 18:32.610
it would become functional
at that point.

18:32.654 --> 18:35.905
I don't know if he'd have
enough time to do it well.

18:35.949 --> 18:38.032
- All right, gentlemen,
you have to make a decision

18:38.076 --> 18:40.159
about who's leaving
the Forge today.

18:40.203 --> 18:41.661
Doug, have you made yours?

18:41.704 --> 18:42.787
- Yes, I have.
- Dave?

18:42.831 --> 18:44.413
- Yeah.
- Jason?

18:44.457 --> 18:46.082
- Yeah, man.
- Let's go tell our smiths.

18:46.126 --> 18:48.292
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

