21:00.510 --> 21:01.968
<i> a pin through</i>
<i> or something like that.</i>

21:02.011 --> 21:04.262
It's not gonna fail on me
like wood would.

21:04.305 --> 21:06.639
The plan in round two
is to try and get

21:06.683 --> 21:09.433
this handle on
as fast as I possibly can.

21:09.477 --> 21:12.311
- How much work does it really
take to put on a hatchet handle?

21:12.355 --> 21:13.938
- It doesn't take
any more time

21:13.982 --> 21:15.690
to put them on than it takes
to put on a knife,

21:15.733 --> 21:18.067
but the time should be
put in indexing that

21:18.111 --> 21:21.237
so that handle feels right
in your hand.

21:21.281 --> 21:22.655
<i> - To me, it's not gonna be</i>
<i> any different</i>

21:22.699 --> 21:24.782
than working with a knife
at this point.

21:24.826 --> 21:26.867
I'm in my comfort zone
big-time.

21:26.911 --> 21:28.536
<i> Based on the judges'</i>
<i> critiques,</i>

21:28.579 --> 21:30.413
<i> I'm gonna need to take</i>
<i> some of the meat off</i>

21:30.456 --> 21:32.039
from somewhere up here

21:32.083 --> 21:33.666
just to make it
a little bit more comfortable.

21:33.710 --> 21:35.376
<i> My hatchet is so big,</i>

21:35.420 --> 21:37.336
