35:49.439 --> 35:51.815
I hope nothing goes wrong
'cause if it does,

35:51.859 --> 35:54.609
I'll have to restart,
and that would really suck.

35:54.653 --> 36:02.409
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:02.452 --> 36:04.494
It survived.
Feeling good.

36:04.538 --> 36:06.329
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:06.373 --> 36:08.331
Now I just got to do the same
thing to the other side.

36:08.375 --> 36:11.585
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:11.628 --> 36:13.128
<i> - Ready to start day three.</i>

36:13.172 --> 36:14.337
<i> I wish I was</i>
<i> a little farther ahead,</i>

36:14.381 --> 36:16.256
but everything is times two,

36:16.300 --> 36:17.966
so whatever I do
to one blade,

36:18.010 --> 36:19.593
<i> it has to be</i>
<i> exactly like the other blade,</i>

36:19.636 --> 36:21.761
and that can be
a challenge in itself.

36:21.805 --> 36:23.388
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:23.432 --> 36:26.141
So I put the first blade
in the jig,

36:26.185 --> 36:28.059
and I can't get it to bend,

36:28.103 --> 36:29.728
<i> so I decide I'm gonna do it</i>
<i> the old-school way</i>

36:29.771 --> 36:31.271
<i> and go back to the anvil.</i>

36:31.315 --> 36:33.899
So it's just gonna be a guess.

36:33.942 --> 36:35.317
<i> Whenever you're dealing</i>
<i> with Damascus,</i>

36:35.360 --> 36:36.860
<i> it's a risky business.</i>

36:36.904 --> 36:38.528
It doesn't always
turn out right.

36:38.572 --> 36:40.488
Nobody makes perfect Damascus
every time they make it.

36:40.532 --> 36:41.740
This is about
a wicked-looking weapon,

36:41.783 --> 36:43.158
I'll tell you what.

36:43.202 --> 36:47.746
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:47.789 --> 36:49.539
<i> - It's day four,</i>
<i> and pretty much all I got left</i>

36:49.583 --> 36:52.709
<i> to do is glue on the handle,</i>
<i> polish that up.</i>

36:52.753 --> 36:55.295
Ray is probably doing
Damascus with his blades,

36:55.339 --> 36:56.922
<i> so I'm trying to be</i>
<i> on the same level.</i>

36:56.965 --> 36:58.757
I'm gonna hand sand.

36:58.800 --> 37:01.593
I'm gonna add file work
on both sides of the handle.

37:01.637 --> 37:04.888
I'm doing, like,
the really fine detail stuff.

37:04.932 --> 37:08.016
<i> I'm going for, like,</i>
<i>a vine pattern on the file work</i>

37:08.060 --> 37:09.392
<i> just to give it</i>
<i> an elegant design,</i>

37:09.436 --> 37:11.186
<i> a little something extra.</i>

37:11.230 --> 37:14.022
I'm kind of just gonna
free-ball it on this one.

37:14.066 --> 37:15.982
It's just about ready to glue.

37:16.026 --> 37:17.108
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:17.152 --> 37:18.485
[blows air]

37:18.528 --> 37:20.570
As soon as I start
mixing the epoxy,

37:20.614 --> 37:22.489
<i> time starts going down.</i>

37:22.532 --> 37:24.199
<i> I only got five minutes</i>
<i> to get everything</i>

37:24.243 --> 37:26.409
<i> where I want it to be</i>
<i> because of the epoxy.</i>

37:26.453 --> 37:29.996
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:30.040 --> 37:32.207
<i> This is the first bump</i>
<i> in the road I run into,</i>

37:32.251 --> 37:34.501
<i> and I feel the time crunch.</i>

37:34.544 --> 37:36.378
Okay.

37:36.421 --> 37:38.338
<i> I finally get it together.</i>

37:38.382 --> 37:39.589
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:39.633 --> 37:41.258
The glue's all set up,

37:41.301 --> 37:43.802
and looks like there's no gaps.

37:43.845 --> 37:46.054
I finished the weapon
a day early.

37:46.098 --> 37:48.348
<i> There was always that thought</i>
<i> in the back of my head</i>

37:48.392 --> 37:50.183
<i> where I'm going</i>
<i> against the best,</i>

37:50.227 --> 37:53.019
but age definitely doesn't
limit your skill.

37:53.063 --> 37:55.397
I'm very proud of this weapon.

37:55.440 --> 37:56.940
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:56.984 --> 37:58.566
<i> - Last day, it's crunch time.</i>

37:58.610 --> 38:00.235
Time to finish it up.

38:00.279 --> 38:01.653
<i> The heat treat went</i>
<i> really well yesterday,</i>

38:01.697 --> 38:03.655
and the blades look good.

38:03.699 --> 38:06.157
<i> First thing I'm gonna do today</i>
<i> is sharpen the blades up</i>

38:06.201 --> 38:07.867
<i> before I assemble them</i>
<i> onto the handle.</i>

38:07.911 --> 38:09.369
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:09.413 --> 38:12.372
I think my skill set
as a Mastersmith

38:12.416 --> 38:14.249
really shows up.
I came here to prove

38:14.293 --> 38:16.334
that I could compete
at a really high level,

38:16.378 --> 38:17.836
<i> and I think that I did that.</i>

38:17.879 --> 38:19.421
<i> The only thing</i>
<i> could stop it is</i>

38:19.464 --> 38:22.549
if my competitor built something
better than I did.

38:22.592 --> 38:24.551
I think it's ready to go.

38:24.594 --> 38:28.888
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:28.932 --> 38:31.558
- Stephen, Ray,
welcome back to the Forge.

38:31.601 --> 38:33.560
You've had five days
at your home forges

38:33.603 --> 38:35.645
to work on your haladies.

38:35.689 --> 38:37.897
Now it's time to see how they
hold up in our weapons test,

38:37.941 --> 38:41.276
but first, Ray, tell us
a little bit about your weapon.

38:41.320 --> 38:44.738
- Well, I made my haladie
as close as I could

38:44.781 --> 38:47.073
<i>to the original type of weapon,</i>

38:47.117 --> 38:49.034
<i> and I made the blades</i>
<i> out of Damascus,</i>

38:49.077 --> 38:51.244
and I think it'll do well.

38:51.288 --> 38:53.621
- Great.
Stephen, tell us about yours.

38:53.665 --> 38:56.499
- I forged mine out of clean
1095 high-carbon steel

38:56.543 --> 38:58.835
<i> and put my own kind</i>
<i> of twist on it</i>

38:58.879 --> 39:01.046
<i> from what of the stuff</i>
<i> I saw on the Internet.</i>

39:01.089 --> 39:03.006
- All right, gentlemen,
your weapons will now

39:03.050 --> 39:05.091
be put through
a series of three tests.

39:05.135 --> 39:08.011
Up first is
the sharpness test.

39:08.055 --> 39:09.346
Doug?

39:09.389 --> 39:11.264
- Bladesmiths,
the haladie was a weapon

39:11.308 --> 39:13.183
used by the Rajput warriors.

39:13.226 --> 39:15.310
It was designed to have a blade
on both sides of the handle,

39:15.354 --> 39:17.354
and they were known
to be very sharp.

39:17.397 --> 39:19.272
To see how sharp
your weapons are,

39:19.316 --> 39:21.608
I will take your blade
and deliver multiple cuts

39:21.651 --> 39:24.069
and stabs
to this canvas bag.

39:24.112 --> 39:25.528
Ray, you're up first.
Are you ready?

39:25.572 --> 39:26.529
- I'm ready.

39:26.573 --> 39:27.530
- Let's do this.

39:27.574 --> 39:30.033
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:30.077 --> 39:31.451
<i> - I'm really proud</i>
<i> of this knife.</i>

39:31.495 --> 39:33.036
I mean, it turned out
really well.

39:33.080 --> 39:35.580
<i> The curvature on the blade</i>
<i> is a recurve,</i>

39:35.624 --> 39:37.749
so what happens is the blade
starts in one direction,

39:37.793 --> 39:39.667
then comes back
in the other direction,

39:39.711 --> 39:41.127
<i> which gives it</i>
<i> a lot of character.</i>

39:41.171 --> 39:47.092
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:52.182 --> 39:53.681
- Okay, Ray.

39:53.725 --> 39:55.558
I like the design
of your blade.

39:55.602 --> 39:57.143
It feels good
in the hand.

39:57.187 --> 39:59.396
You got that ovoid shape
for the handle,

39:59.439 --> 40:01.231
and I like also
how it flares over there

40:01.274 --> 40:03.900
so it stops
for the thrust.

40:03.944 --> 40:06.945
I love your recurve
and Damascus pattern

40:06.988 --> 40:09.489
that you have
on both ends of your blade.

40:09.533 --> 40:13.034
It's very dramatic,
and it looks good.

40:13.078 --> 40:18.289
The belly of your blade
slashed nicely on the canvas,

40:18.333 --> 40:20.959
and it allowed
for a good thrust,

40:21.002 --> 40:24.129
and this blade will cut.
Good job.

40:24.172 --> 40:25.463
- Thank you.

40:25.507 --> 40:26.923
- Stephen, you're up next.
You ready?

40:26.967 --> 40:28.341
- Hell, yeah.
- Let's do this.

40:28.385 --> 40:32.679
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:32.722 --> 40:34.973
<i> - Going up</i>
<i> against a master bladesmith</i>

40:35.016 --> 40:37.183
with 30 years' experience
is definitely

40:37.227 --> 40:39.894
<i> a little nerve-racking for me,</i>
<i> but I'm pretty sure</i>

40:39.938 --> 40:43.231
<i> I got everything executed</i>
<i> perfectly on it.</i>

40:43.275 --> 40:47.861
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:47.904 --> 40:50.321
- Well, Stephen,

40:50.365 --> 40:51.739
we have a big problem here.

40:51.783 --> 40:54.534
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:58.915 --> 41:05.795
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:06.882 --> 41:08.465
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:08.508 --> 41:10.884
- Well, Stephen,

41:10.927 --> 41:13.803
we have a big problem here.

41:13.847 --> 41:15.430
- What's the problem?

41:15.474 --> 41:19.726
- We specifically asked
for a recurve on each blade.

41:19.769 --> 41:22.353
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:22.397 --> 41:25.398
These blades are not recurved.

41:25.442 --> 41:27.025
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:27.068 --> 41:29.152
They're simply curved.

41:29.196 --> 41:31.237
We put that specifically
on our parameters

41:31.281 --> 41:33.198
so that both blades
are equal and fair

41:33.241 --> 41:35.492
in all the tests that we do.

41:35.535 --> 41:38.244
Your blade does not have
that S-shape recurve

41:38.288 --> 41:39.454
that we're looking for.

41:39.498 --> 41:42.165
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:42.209 --> 41:44.542
Because you don't have
that S-shape recurve

41:44.586 --> 41:46.044
that we needed
for the parameters,

41:46.087 --> 41:47.754
we cannot move on
to test your blade.

41:47.797 --> 41:50.590
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:50.634 --> 41:53.801
- Well, Stephen,
the devil's in the details.

41:53.845 --> 41:55.970
The blade parameters
were very specific.

41:56.014 --> 41:59.390
We asked for counter recurve
blades on your haladie.

41:59.434 --> 42:01.017
You didn't deliver that.

42:01.061 --> 42:03.269
Therefore, since your weapon
cannot be tested

42:03.313 --> 42:05.313
fairly and evenly,

42:05.357 --> 42:07.106
I must ask you
to please leave the Forge.

42:07.150 --> 42:08.316
- Okay.

42:08.360 --> 42:11.903
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:11.947 --> 42:13.947
I'm feeling a little bummed.
I put in all that hard work,

42:13.990 --> 42:15.823
and I didn't even get
to test it.

42:15.867 --> 42:17.534
<i> I still feel really proud</i>
<i> of my work.</i>

42:17.577 --> 42:21.663
It's just I failed to see
the one small detail,

42:21.706 --> 42:25.333
and that led me to losing.

42:25.377 --> 42:27.961
I learned I got to follow the
instructions a little better.

42:28.004 --> 42:30.088
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:30.131 --> 42:31.422
- Ray, congratulations.

42:31.466 --> 42:32.882
You are the "Forged in Fire"
champion

42:32.926 --> 42:35.260
and will be receiving
a check for $10,000.

42:35.303 --> 42:37.929
Good job.
[applause]

42:37.973 --> 42:39.430
- Thank you.

42:39.474 --> 42:41.266
- It's a good-looking
weapon, sir.

42:41.309 --> 42:42.642
- Thank you.

42:42.686 --> 42:44.435
<i>- I love your Damascus pattern,</i>

42:44.479 --> 42:46.896
really, really nice recurve
with beautiful shape.

42:46.940 --> 42:47.897
- How you feel right now?

42:47.941 --> 42:49.399
- Feeling really good.

42:49.442 --> 42:51.067
<i> Being "Forged in Fire"</i>
<i> champion,</i>

42:51.111 --> 42:54.237
it's really nice,
especially at my age.

42:54.281 --> 42:55.947
<i> I'd have felt a lot better</i>
<i> about it if it--you know,</i>

42:55.991 --> 42:57.782
<i> if they could have did</i>
<i> the cutting contest</i>

42:57.826 --> 42:59.617
<i> and everything</i>
<i> with his blade also,</i>

42:59.661 --> 43:02.662
but I just sold a knife
for 10,000 bucks.

43:02.706 --> 43:03.913
That's the best part.

